# Session mode keywords (operator shorthand)

**Language:** Keywords in this table are **English-only tokens**. The operator types them **as written** (e.g. `deps`, `pmo-view`, `study-check`) even when the rest of the message is pt-BR—no Portuguese spellings or synonyms for these cues in rules or committed docs. Chat **narration** may stay pt-BR per **`AGENTS.md`**.

Single-word cues set **session scope**. Prefer **one mode per branch/PR** unless the user explicitly combines tracks.

| Keyword              | Scope                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | Primary references                                                   |
| -------              | -----                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | -------------------                                                  |
| **deps**             | Dependency maintenance: edit **`pyproject.toml`** → **`uv lock`** → **`uv export --no-emit-package pyproject.toml -o requirements.txt`** → **`.\scripts\check-all.ps1`**. Triage Dependabot/security deps per **`SECURITY.md`** and **`.cursor/rules/dependabot-hygiene.mdc`**.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          | `docs/plans/PLANS_TODO.md` (order **–1**)                            |
| **feature**          | Product work: one slice from **`PLANS_TODO.md`** (“What to start next”) + linked **`docs/plans/PLAN_*.md`**. Tests + operator docs as needed; refresh plan rows / dashboard when the slice completes.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    | Plans + **`.\scripts\check-all.ps1`**                                |
| **homelab**          | Production-readiness smoke on a **second environment** (manual). Operator runs **`docs/ops/HOMELAB_VALIDATION.md`** (and **`.pt_BR`** if used). Agent helps with **doc/checklist fixes** or small script tweaks from what you find—not running your hardware.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            | `PLANS_TODO.md` (order **–1L**)                                      |
| **docs**             | **Documentation-only** passes: guides (**USAGE**, **DEPLOY**, **TECH_GUIDE**, **SECURITY**, pt-BR pairs per policy), README/pitch (**`.cursor/rules/pitch-roadmap-sync.mdc`**), plan prose, broken links. Follow **`.cursor/rules/docs-policy.mdc`**. If **`PLANS_TODO.md`** status table rows change, run **`python scripts/plans-stats.py --write`**. For **CLI /help / man** drift, see **`docs/OPERATOR_HELP_AUDIT.md`**, rule **`operator-help-sync.mdc`**, tests **`tests/test_operator_help_sync.py`**. No behavior change unless correcting docs that describe wrong behavior.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   | `docs/`, `docs/plans/`                                               |
| **houseclean**       | **Hygiene** without a new product feature: branch/remote cleanup playbook (**`docs/ops/BRANCH_AND_DOCKER_CLEANUP.md`**), **`plans-stats`** refresh, Ruff/format (pre-commit), optional **`scripts/maintenance-check.ps1`**, small safe refactors, dead code, script/ignore consistency. Batch coherent edits; **`check-all`** before merge. Avoid mixing with large **deps** or **feature** slices in one PR unless the user asks.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       | Ops docs + **`check-all`**                                           |
| **backlog**          | **Triage / remember-later**, not a default implementation pass: scan **`PLANS_TODO.md`** (Deferred, §H3 catalogue, Wabbix optional rows, “Follow-ups”), per-plan **`⬜ Pending`** tables, **`docs/OPERATOR_HELP_AUDIT.md`** checkboxes, queued issues (e.g. Dependabot **#105**). Outcome is usually a **short list, reprioritisation, or one cherry-picked slice** promoted to **`feature`** / **`deps`** / **`docs`**. Avoid starting multi-plan coding unless the user names one item.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 | `PLANS_TODO.md`, `docs/plans/PLAN_*.md`, audit docs                  |
| **`pmo-view`**       | **Plan / PMO docs in readable form.** The assistant **cannot** switch Cursor to **Markdown Preview** (rendered) for you—that is an **editor** action. When the operator says **`pmo-view`** (or “**pmo view**” / “**open plans in preview**”): (1) **Lead the reply** with the **preview shortcuts**: **Windows/Linux:** `Ctrl+Shift+V` (preview tab) or `Ctrl+K` then `V` (preview beside source); **macOS:** `Cmd+Shift+V` / `Cmd+K` `V`. (2) **List** the usual PMO/plan files with workspace paths so they can open them: **`docs/plans/PLANS_TODO.md`**, **`docs/plans/SPRINTS_AND_MILESTONES.md`** (+ **`.pt_BR.md`** if they prefer pt-BR), **`docs/plans/TOKEN_AWARE_USAGE.md`**, **`docs/ops/COMMIT_AND_PR.md`** (+ **`.pt_BR`**), and **`docs/ops/OPERATOR_LAB_DOCUMENT_MAP.md`** (+ **`.pt_BR`**) when lab/doc-map context applies. (3) Optionally **`read_file`** one file if they asked for a specific section—format the answer with clear headings so the **chat panel** stays readable; still remind them **Preview** is sharper for tables and Mermaid. | Same paths; **`.cursor/rules/session-mode-keywords.mdc`** (this row) |
| **`study-check`**    | **Study cadence recap (operator-requested).** When the operator types **`study-check`**: give a **compact** reminder of the agreed weekly rhythm (**2** CWL + **1** AI → **2** CWL + **1** other, repeat), **CWL sequence** (**BTF → C3SA** then §3.2), and pointers to **`docs/plans/PORTFOLIO_AND_EVIDENCE_SOURCES.md`** §3.0–§3.2, **`docs/ops/OPERATOR_MANUAL_ACTIONS.md`** (+ **`.pt_BR`**) §1, **`docs/plans/SPRINTS_AND_MILESTONES.md`** §3.1. **Narration** may be pt-BR per **`AGENTS.md`**. See **`.cursor/rules/study-cadence-reminders.mdc`** for when the assistant may surface the same **without** the keyword (natural breakpoints only).                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                | **`.cursor/rules/study-cadence-reminders.mdc`**                      |
| **`glossary-check`** | **Glossary navigation/update cue.** When the operator types **`glossary-check`**, prioritize glossary-aware help: (1) open pointers to **`docs/GLOSSARY.md`** and **`docs/GLOSSARY.pt_BR.md`**; (2) list candidate new terms found in recent edits; (3) propose concise definitions in EN first + pt-BR sync; (4) verify links from external-facing docs remain audience-safe.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | `docs/GLOSSARY.md`, `docs/GLOSSARY.pt_BR.md`                         |

**Commit taxonomy:** **`docs`** and **`houseclean`** usually map to **`documentation`** or **`workflow`** commits in **`.cursor/rules/execution-priority-and-pr-batching.mdc`**; keep intent explicit in commit messages.
